/**
 * Spaced Repetition System (SRS) Algorithm Documentation
 * 
 * The system uses a modified SM-2 (SuperMemo-2) algorithm integrated with
 * RPG-style character stats and survival mechanics.
 * 
 * 1. Core Algorithm (FSRS-inspired SM-2):
 *    - Ease Factor (EF) & Stability Modeling: Determines how much the interval increases.
 *    - Quality (Q): User-reported recall quality (0: Again, 3: Hard, 4: Good, 5: Easy).
 *    - Retention Goal: Algorithms are optimized for a 90% retention rate.
 * 
 * 2. Circadian Rhythm Factor (Time of Day):
 *    - Focus Peak: 10:00 AM (Search/Identification focus).
 *    - Consolidation Peak: 07:00 PM (Long-term encoding focus).
 *    - Late Night Penalty (01:00 AM - 05:00 AM): Significant stability drop due to sleep deprivation.
 *    - Prime-Time Nudge: Reviews are automatically scheduled toward these peaks to maximize success.
 * 
 * 3. Fatigue & Cognitive Load:
 *    - Fatigue accumulates based on session duration, mistakes, and biological dips.
 *    - Endurance (E) stat increases stamina.
 *    - Session Persistence: Repeated failures in the same session result in stability dampening (avoiding short-term memory illusions).
 * 
 * 4. Character Stat Integration:
 *    - Intelligence (I): Improves learning efficiency (stability gain rate).
 *    - Endurance (E): Reduces fatigue accumulation (the "Burnout Threshold").
 *    - Luck (L): Chance for "Critical Recall" (significant interval boost).
 *    - Perception (P): Improves focus during morning clarity periods.
 *    - Agility (A): Speeds up reflexive recall for "Easy" cards.
 * 
 * 5. Learning Lapses:
 *    - Total Lapses (L): Difficulty increases exponentially with each reset, requiring more frequent reviews to stabilize.
 */
